      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI for primary QoI (NIH) must be below 5% on the production mesh.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed with refinement ratio r = 1.5. Richardson extrapolation yields GCI = 4.1% for NIH at worst-case operating point. Production mesh (6.8 M cells) selected as medium mesh, balancing accuracy and computational cost. Discretization error bounded within acceptance threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must be documented and traceable to COU operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments sourced from FDA benchmark dataset (Hariharan et al. 2011). Test conditions documented: flow rates 2.5–7.0 LPM, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM, fluid temperature 37°C, hematocrit 30%. All five validation operating points fall within the COU operating envelope. Test condition traceability established."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., mean relative error or validation metric u_val) must be computed against experimental data with uncertainty quantification, achieving level 3 rigor including propagation of both numerical and experimental uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison performed using mean relative error (MRE = 8.3%) across five operating points. Experimental uncertainty bands sourced from published FDA dataset (±15% NIH). CFD predictions fall within experimental uncertainty at all five points. The comparison is reported as a point-wise relative error metric; however, a formal validation metric incorporating combined numerical and experimental uncertainty propagation per ASME V&V 20 was not computed. The assessment team judged the qualitative agreement and conservative acceptance margin sufficient to conclude validation adequacy, and the factor was recorded as satisfactorily addressed for MRL 2 purposes."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoIs must be directly relevant to the COU decision quantity (hemolysis index).",
      "rationale": "Primary validation QoI is normalized index of hemolysis (NIH), directly related to the COU decision quantity (relative hemolysis index RH). Secondary QoI is pump head-flow curve, confirming hydraulic fidelity. Both QoIs are directly relevant to worst-case hemolysis identification. Relevance requirement satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry and operating conditions must be sufficiently similar to the COU device and operating envelope to support extrapolation of validation conclusions.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal blood pump, a representative geometry for the Class II CPB device class. Operating conditions span the COU envelope. Geometric similarity assessed via non-dimensional parameters (specific speed Ns, tip clearance ratio). Validation activities judged sufficiently relevant to support COU conclusions at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence must be demonstrated with residuals below solver-recommended thresholds.",
      "rationale": "All simulations converged to residuals below 1e-5 for continuity and momentum equations. Mass imbalance below 0.01%. Convergence monitored via NIH monitor point stabilization over final 500 iterations. Numerical solver error requirements at level 1 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup must be reviewed by a qualified independent analyst prior to production runs.",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup independently reviewed by a senior CFD analyst not involved in case preparation. Boundary conditions, material properties (non-Newtonian blood rheology, Carreau model), and hemolysis power-law model parameters verified against published sources. No setup errors identified. Use error level 1 requirements satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis damage model selection must be justified with reference to published literature for blood pump applications.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published benchmarking studies for blood pump applications (Hariharan et al. 2011, Fraser et al. 2012). Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model applied with Heuser-Opitz modified coefficients. Model form uncertainty discussed and judged acceptable for relative comparison purposes. Level 2 requirements satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters must be traceable to published sources or direct measurement, with uncertainty ranges documented.",
      "rationale": "Blood density (1056 kg/m3), Carreau viscosity parameters, and hemolysis model coefficients sourced from peer-reviewed literature with full citations. Geometric inputs derived from FDA benchmark CAD files. Inlet velocity profiles derived from flow meter measurements. Input uncertainty ranges documented in credibility plan appendix. Level 2 requirements satisfied."
    },
